President Biden has announced his intention to appoint commissioners to the President's Advisory Commission on Asian Americans, Native Hawaiians, and Pacific Islanders. The commission will focus on advancing equity and opportunity for the AANHPI community, addressing anti-Asian xenophobia and violence, and tackling intersectional barriers faced by AANHPI women, LGBTQ+ individuals, and people with disabilities. The commission will consist of civic leaders from across the country and will represent the diverse AANHPI communities in the United States. The appointed leaders include Amy Agbayani, Teresita Batayola, Ajay Bhutoria, Luisa Blue, Kimberly Chang, Emily Chen, Kerry Doi, Grace Huang, Victoria Huynh, Mia Ives-Rublee, Kamal Kalsi, Michelle Kauhane, Daniel Dae Kim, Kevin Kim, Sarah Min, Simon Pang, Ai-jen Poo, Naheed Qureshi, Raynald Samoa, Sonal Shah, Smita Shah, Robert Underwood, and KaYing Yang. Each leader brings expertise and experience in various fields such as education, healthcare, community advocacy, and more.